JOHANNESBURG - Satellite television provider Multichoice is being probed by the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (Icasa). The probe relates to several payments made by Multichoice to both the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) and ANN7. The payments were allegedly made to sway government policy on digital migration in favour of Multichoice. READ: Multichoice paid SABC R100-million: DA Icasa says the matter has been referred to its Compliance and Consumer Affairs Division. The Gupta leaks last year revealed dodgy payments Multichoice had made to ANN7. READ: MultiChoice launches corruption probe The payments amounted to hundreds of millions of rand. eNCA